Abstract

This dissertation establishes a mathematically rigorous theory of universal intelligence as an anti-entropic, provably-safe, resource-bounded optimization process. Building upon enriched category theory, information geometry, fixed-point dynamics, and dependent type theory, we introduce four critical innovations:

1. Enriched intentional operators over the cost quantale ([0,\infty],\geq,+,0), yielding a functorial bridge between categorical composition and geometric optimization, with a quantified bound relating cost and metric distortion.
2. \epsilon-idempotency via \epsilon-monads, proving that the Fisher distance between \mathfrak{I}^2 and \mathfrak{I} is bounded by available resources R, ensuring robust intentional closure under approximation.
3. Proof-carrying beliefs through dependent types \{q:\mathcal{M}\mid\varphi(q)\} and Hoare logic, enabling end-to-end formal verification of safety invariants preserved by intentional updates; proof complexity scales polynomially with dimension and logarithmically with resource bounds.
4. Curvature–plasticity duality and the Optimal Curvature Theorem, establishing a fundamental trade-off between sectional curvature of the belief manifold and learning efficiency, with an explicit Goldilocks zone [\kappa_{\min}^*,\kappa_{\max}^*] that maximizes information capacity while stabilizing gradient-based optimization; the interval is proven to exist and to contain zero under mild conditions.

We derive a hierarchical active inference architecture with temporal scale separation \Delta t^{(\ell)} = \kappa^\ell \Delta t^{(0)}, and prove existence, uniqueness, and convergence of \epsilon-proximal fixed points under resource constraints. A concrete instantiation on the manifold of multivariate Gaussians yields closed-form curvature expressions, correcting earlier misconceptions about constant negative curvature. All theorems are stated with explicit constants and qualified by additive \epsilon(R)-terms, ensuring mathematical honesty and practical applicability. This work provides the first unified foundation for provably-safe, resource-efficient, universally-capable intelligent systems.

Keywords: Enriched Category Theory, Information Geometry, \epsilon-Monads, Dependent Types, Proof-Carrying Code, Curvature–Plasticity Duality, Active Inference, Formal Verification, Resource-Bounded Rationality, Anti-Entropic Dynamics.

