When curvature falls outside the optimal interval, the \epsilon-proximal iteration may fail to converge in finite resources. For instance, if \sec < -\kappa with \kappa large, sample complexity is low but optimization can become chaotic; if \sec > \kappa large, convergence is fast but sample complexity explodes, making it impossible to achieve high accuracy with finite data. These boundaries delimit the framework's applicability.

