9.2 Combined Lyapunov–Hoare Verification

Definition 9.3 (Verified Lyapunov Function). A function V: \mathcal{M} \to \mathbb{R}_+ is a verified Lyapunov function for dynamics \Phi if:

1. V(q) = 0 \iff q = q^* (unique equilibrium);
2. \mathcal{L}_\Phi V(q) \leq -\alpha V(q) + \beta (Lyapunov condition in differential form);
3. \vdash \{V(q) \leq r\} \ \Phi \ \{V(q') \leq e^{-\alpha t}r + \beta/\alpha\} (Hoare triple for the discrete-time update).

